{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"86651516-9995-41c5-ac96-067cc2628958","content":"Here's what I know about .NET MAUI safe area handling:\n\n**1. `ios:Page.UseSafeArea=\"True\"` — ✅ Correct**\n\nThis is the standard approach. You need the namespace declaration:\n\n```xml\nxmlns:ios=\"clr-namespace:Microsoft.Maui.Controls.PlatformConfiguration.iOSSpecific;assembly=Microsoft.Maui.Controls\"\n```\n\nOr in C#: `On<iOS>().SetUseSafeArea(true);`\n\nThis remains valid in .NET 10.\n\n**2. `IgnoreSafeArea=\"True\"` on a Grid — ❌ Not a standard MAUI property**\n\nThere is no built-in `IgnoreSafeArea` property on layout views in .NET MAUI. Your tutorial may be outdated (Xamarin-era) or referencing a third-party library.\n\n**For a background image extending into the safe area**, the common patterns are:\n\n- Place the image **outside** the safe-area-respecting layout (e.g., use an `AbsoluteLayout` or `Grid` as the page root without `UseSafeArea`, layer the background image behind a content container that has manual safe-area padding).\n- Or don't set `UseSafeArea` on the page and apply padding selectively:\n\n```xml\n<ContentPage xmlns:ios=\"...\"\n             ios:Page.UseSafeArea=\"False\">\n    <Grid>\n        <!-- Background image fills entire screen -->\n        <Image Source=\"bg.png\" Aspect=\"AspectFill\" />\n        <!-- Content respects safe area via padding -->\n        <VerticalStackLayout Padding=\"{OnPlatform iOS='20,60,20,34'}\">\n            <!-- your content -->\n        </VerticalStackLayout>\n    </Grid>\n</ContentPage>\n```\n\nFor dynamic safe area values, you can read `SafeAreaInsets` from the platform at runtime via the iOS-specific APIs.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"cf373c2f-b466-44d0-bde1-2cc6d20c48b6","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about .NET MAUI safe area handling on iOS, specifically about two properties:\n1. `ios:Page.UseSafeArea=\"True\"` on ContentPage\n2. `IgnoreSafeArea=\"True\"` on a Grid\n\nLet 